Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using visual attention models to train a convolutional network for self-driving vehicles. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep neural perception and control networks for self-driving vehicles. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the end-to-end training of a convolutional network and the use of attention-based models. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper focuses on self-driving vehicles, which are a type of robot. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of a video-to-text model to produce textual explanations of model actions.
